          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683206721424-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> flour mixture</strong></p><p>Pat the <strong>hake fillets</strong> dry with kitchen<strong> </strong>paper</p><p>Add the <strong>hake fillets </strong>to the floured plate and turn several times until they are fully coated – this is your <strong>coated hake</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683206725692-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683206725692-x400.jpg",
